75 % of the professionals working mothers had problems because of their mothers
discrimination at work has increased over the past few years , particularly for women of younger generations that want to be mothers .
shows that the study " fertility and women 's professional career in spain , " carried out by the csic together with the instituto de mujer .
the survey , conducted on 9 737 women from 15 to 75 years , that leaves no room for doubt : 75 % of working mothers have seen their professional career limited because of the babies .
the study indicates that there are many differences regarding the early life couple , and the number of children , whether or not the woman works and occupied the kind of job .
those who do not work outside the home , work part time work or have little stable , reached earlier in a partnership , and have more children have their first pregnancy earlier .
however , women who have a stable job , mostly in the public sector , reject the entry into the living couple , and the first pregnancy , and having fewer children .
women between 35 and 49 years with a fixed work have their first child , on average , 3.7 years after having built in couple . that figure rises to 4.1 in those who work in the public sector . " these data show that women have a stable job was needed more time in their lives for that , which led them to reject the union and the arrival of the children .
more broadly , the kind of employment exercised influence the maternity leave , but less common date of life , " explains the chercheuse the csic margarita delgado .
the education level is another factor which is widening the gap in the age of marriage of women and their first child .
according to the survey , the higher the level of training , the more they are marient and have their first child later .
the difference is also maintains among women of the same generation .
for example , in the group with between 35 and 49 years , those who have made higher basic studies and mothers were respectively for the first time in 25,1 and 32,1 years on average .
" another disctinction is also among the women , according to their level of education .
while those who have done basic studies marient and have their first child had to find a stable job , those studies of average level or above reverse this program and give priority to obtain a stable work as a condition for marriage and the arrival of a child , " says mrs delgado .
